        <a name="Contact_and_Bug_Reports"></a>
        <h2>
            Contact and Bug Reports
        </h2>
        <p>
            For support issues, please email <a href="mailto:monotools@novell.com" class='external'
                title="mailto:monotools@novell.com" rel="nofollow">monotools@novell.com</a>,
            or use the <a href="http://mono-tools.com/contact/" title="http://mono-tools.com/contact/"
                rel="nofollow">Mono Tools for Visual Studio Contact form</a> to contact the
            Mono Tools team at Novell directly.
        </p>
        <p>
            If you believe you have discovered a bug in Mono or the Mono Tools for Visual Studio,
            please use Novell's Bugzilla to enter bug reports and to search for existing reports.
            The <a href="http://mono-project.com/Bugs" title="Bugs">Mono Bugs</a> page provides
            links to search and create bug reports for the various Mono components.
        </p>
        <p>
            Some useful resources for using Novell's Bugzilla bug tracking system:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="https://bugzilla.novell.com/index.cgi" class='external' title="https://bugzilla.novell.com/index.cgi"
                rel="nofollow">Novell's Bugzilla</a> </li>
            <li><a href="http://mono-project.com/FAQ:_Novell_Bugzilla" class='external' title="FAQ: Novell Bugzilla">
                How to create a Novell.com account</a> </li>
            <li><a href="http://mono-project.com/Bugs#How_to_make_a_good_bug_report" class='external'
                title="">How to make a good bug report</a> </li>
        </ul>
